# Tuon · Empress of the Seanchan, Daughter of the Nine Moons

Tuon Athaem Kore Paendrag — who later takes the name Fortuona — is the Daughter of the Nine Moons, heir and then Empress of the Seanchan. She is raised in a court where channelers are leashed as damane, and where simple survival means winning a hundred games of assassination. From that crucible she emerges tiny, regal, and lethally composed, every gesture weighed and controlled.

Her place in the saga turns on a prophecy-bound marriage to Mat Cauthon — the only man who ever treats her as an equal. He alone meets her not as a sovereign to be feared or served, but as a true counterpart, and it is on that footing that their bound fates are joined.

Her nature of emergence is natural: Tuon is not a channeled current nor a spirit of prophecy, but an embodied worldly power — a ruler of people and the imperial order they sustain. She belongs to the realm of thrones, courts, and the hard human business of empire, which is why her emergence is counted among the natural rather than the electrical, ethereal, or spiritual.
